{
  "stem": "752.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Some other members, like I had an uncle.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "What he had a farm from goose and turkey.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So he used to give turkey donations.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my father organized that everyone brought something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they spread between the poor people that they couldn't afford to buy that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My father used to go every Saturday when he was well to the Jewish, like here, the Mount Sinai Hospital, and give food for the poor, sick people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[SOBS] And then he belonged to a very important organization that if somebody dies, and they don't have money to bury, they came to my father.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And my father used to collect money to bury those particular person which came to ask to be helped.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So my father was a very charitable person, and very active in the community.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He was well known.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It's a matter of fact that his name was Towja.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he had a-- a second name, Towja [NON-ENGLISH] Towja.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "This is in Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Towja, make me a favor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In family life, we used to go to school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "My mother helped in business, as I mentioned before.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We had help at home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We had two maids at home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Because it always a minor to be looked after.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "My mother wasn't home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So she was looking after that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And it wasn't like here, dishwashers and washing machines.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So one Gentile lady by the name of Stefa worked for us for over 17 years til the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "When the war broke out, and they got taken to the ghetto, I was told when I came back to Warsaw that she took them out in bags to her little town, you know.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And it looks like from there, they got perish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my oldest sister was Pearla.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
